title: The Bitchographies: Random Commentaries About Life, Love, and Knockoff Christian Louboutins
description: Tired of following a complicated script of dos and donâ€™ts, Vuitton bares all in her hilariously unfiltered vignettes. Nothing is off-limits, from dating disasters to botched Botox, calculating colleagues to fake friends, and so much more!

title: Losing the Atmosphere, A Memoir: A Baffling Disorder, a Search for Help, and the Therapist Who Understood
description: Born in 1940s Brooklyn, Vivian Conan grew up in two different worlds. Outside, she had friends, excelled in school; inside, she saw faces that weren't hers in her bedroom mirror that bathed her in the love and understanding she craved. Told with honesty, humor, and grace, Losing the Atmosphere is Vivian Conan's riveting account of her journey toward wholeness.  2021 Independent Audiobook Awards Finalist and Independent Press Awards Distinguished Favorite.

title: The Pursued and the Pursuing
description: While F. Scott Fitzgerald's The Great Gatsby ends after Jay Gatsby is shot and killed, The Pursued and the Pursuing explores what might have been had it left Gatsby with another chance at happiness. Find it he does, although not in the arms of Daisy Buchanan.
